    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 101 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commanding General, United States Military Mission in the
                        Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Deane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Commanding General, Twelfth Army
                        Group</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BGON1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bradley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d101fn1">The portion of
                            the message omitted here summarizes <ref target="#d98">document No.
                                98</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-26">26 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_BGON1">General Bradley</persName> and to <persName
                        corresp="#p_MGAGC1">General Marshall</persName> for his <gloss
                        target="#t_EyesOnly1">eyes only</gloss> citing <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >Shges</hi> [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] from <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1"
                        >Deane</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_topsec1">top sec</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_MX1">MX</gloss> 24797.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>We have already emphasized the importance of <persName corresp="#p_SMGFE1"
                        >General Stoner</persName>’s proceeding to Berlin for the signal
                    installations when we asked for authority to increase <persName
                        corresp="#p_PMGFL1">Parks</persName>’ group.</p>
                <p>Upon receipt of your <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> 93051<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d101fn2">
                        <ref target="#d96">Document No. 96</ref>.</note> last night, I again
                    presented the matter to <persName corresp="#p_AAGAI1">General Antonov</persName>
                    and <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName> presented it to <persName
                        corresp="#p_V2">Vyshinski</persName>.<note n="3" xml:id="d101fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d97">document No. 97</ref>.</note> I shall see <persName
                        corresp="#p_AAGAI1">General Antonov</persName> or his representatives today
                    and press the matter further.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
